{"type":"message","id":"97d96e62","parentId":"4a4d732d","timestamp":"2026-03-15T07:47:07.515Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The read tool can't list directories. I need to use the process tool with a session. Let me create a session first and then run commands. Looking at the process tool more carefully, it seems like I need to use action that doesn't require sessionId for initial execution. Let me check if there's a way to spawn a new session.\n\nActually, looking at the process tool description again: \"Manage running exec sessions: list, poll, log, write, send-keys, submit, paste, kill.\" It seems like sessions need to be created somehow. Let me try using a different approach - maybe I can use the session status or try to run commands differently.\n\nLet me try to use process with different actions to see if I can get a session started.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_7e2b0526e95a40f5816f0ccd","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"list"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"dashscope-coding","model":"qwen3.5-plus","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773560822241}}
